Here’s a structured list of questions that a Proof of Concept (PoC) for AI in test automation can help answer. These are typically the key uncertainties teams want to validate before investing further:


---

🔍 Feasibility & Capability

Can AI automatically generate test cases from requirements or user stories?

How accurately can AI understand acceptance criteria or specs?

Can AI identify edge cases better than traditional approaches?

Is AI capable of maintaining test scripts when the UI changes?

Can AI generate meaningful assertions without human input?



---

⚙️ Efficiency & Productivity

How much time can AI save in test creation vs manual scripting?

Can AI reduce test maintenance effort over time?

Does AI speed up regression testing cycles?

How much faster can test suites be generated and executed?



---

🧠 Intelligence & Adaptability

Can AI detect flaky tests and suggest fixes?

How well does AI adapt to frequent UI/UX changes?

Can AI prioritize test cases based on risk or usage patterns?

Is AI able to learn from past defects and improve coverage?



---

🧪 Test Coverage & Quality

Does AI increase overall test coverage?

Can AI identify gaps in existing test suites?

How effective is AI in detecting real defects vs false positives?

Can AI simulate real user behavior for better testing?



---

🔄 Integration & Compatibility

Can AI integrate with existing CI/CD pipelines?

Does it work with current test frameworks (e.g., Selenium, Playwright)?

How easily can AI tools plug into existing DevOps workflows?

Does AI support multiple environments and platforms?



---

💰 Cost & ROI

What is the cost of implementing AI-driven test automation?

What ROI can be expected compared to traditional automation?

How much manual effort can be reduced (in %)?

Does AI reduce long-term maintenance costs?



---

🔐 Reliability & Risk

How reliable are AI-generated test results?

What is the false positive / false negative rate?

Can AI explain why a test failed (traceability)?

Are there risks of over-reliance on AI?



---

👩‍💻 Usability & Adoption

How easy is it for QA engineers to use AI tools?

What level of expertise is required to operate the solution?

How steep is the learning curve?

Can non-technical stakeholders leverage AI-generated insights?



---

📊 Reporting & Insights

Can AI provide actionable insights from test results?

Does it generate intelligent reports and dashboards?

Can AI predict defect-prone areas of the application?

How well does it support root cause analysis?



---

🚀 Scalability & Future Readiness

Can the AI solution scale with growing test suites?

How well does it perform with large and complex applications?

Can it support cross-browser and cross-device testing?

Is the solution future-proof with evolving AI capabilities?



